text:
"So many people want to project their life onto you and it's irrelevant"
- Alex Hormozi 

99% of us are living lives based on other people's opinions. What we drive, what we wear, who we're friends with, our standards, our beliefs, what we do for a living.... the list goes on and on. 

When you stop chasing other people's dreams and live life on your terms... you've won. 

Not just today but you've won life. 

Live life how YOU want, then determine what success looks like for YOU. 

That's where you'll find happiness

Mozination – 
Over the past few weeks, I removed “I have nothing to sell you” from all my social media profiles and 114 YT videos. And no, it’s not because I have some course I’m selling.

Reason: I have a book for sale for .99. And even though Amazon takes .66 of the .99 (lol), it’s still factually false.

You probably know me well enough by now - language precision matters a lot to me. So, since I technically have something “for sale” I will be removing it.

I want to be clear - my intention remains unchanged - I make the vast majority of my wealth from the companies we invest in - and I make this content to attract more 1% companies to invest in while giving to the 99% without an ask.

Good news: Without this technicality, it opens me up to provide some of the things y’all have been asking for: some hats and meetups for #mozination without worrying that I am ‘defying’ my core principle of giving.

My ask for Mozination: Please don’t refer to me as someone who has “nothing to sell” since it’s not technically true. I just want everyone on the same page.

What to expect now: Same as before - as much free content as I can muster to help you scale your businesses…and maybe a few hats 😉

Keep crushing. Appreciate you all,
Alex

PS - And of course -  if you’ve got a company doing over $3M-$100M in sales and want our help scaling it, go to: acquisition.com/apply
Another value nugget I agree with from Alex Hormozi
#neverskipdessert

Are you making videos for your niche and want them to go viral?

Well, I got news for you...

If you're making this big mistake chances are they never will 😱

The algorithm on Tiktok is interested based.

This means Tiktok will only show your video to people that are actually interested in it.

So if you're only making content in a very defined niche...

Chances are there isn't a large enough audience to rack in millions of views.

For example, if you only talk about real estate guess what?

The majority of people online actually find real estate boring. 

So the platform is going to limit the number of people that will see the video.

Following so far?

So if you want to go viral you need to ditch niche topis and start with a general.

THEN tie in your niche.

That way the platform can send your video to just about everyone while still giving basically the same info.

An easy general topic that you can immediately implement into your content strategy is talking about relationships.

For example, we all know Alex Hormozi for his business advice.

But one of his videos that got 4.1 MILLION VIEWS is on how he convinces his wife to go where he wants for dinner.

Hidden behind the general topic is sales advice.

You can watch the video below to see what I mean.

Moral of the story:

Start with a general topic, then tie in your niche.

This is the first cause of virality.

There are 4 in total.

Over the next few days, I'll share the next 3!

Cool? Stay tuned!

-      Sam

PS. Need help creating 90 days of videos like the one below without coming up with the ideas, editing or posting? Then stay tuned for Black Friday 😉

PPS. Shoutout to Alex Hormozi for the amazing content!

text:
https://youtu.be/lNpISjniwLU

Key Takeaways from an interview with Alex Hormozi and Ryan Pineda.

1. "Only Losers should fear a recession. If you are a winner all that will happen is you will eat everyone's lunch" Continue doing the same thing you have always done, when others pull back you will automatically begin taking shares of the industry.

2. Two indicators to a successful CEO. 1st Ego is in check. 2nd Emotional reactivity is in control.

3. Weather short term discomfort for long term achievement.

What I gained from this short interview was: 

1. Continue doing the basics, control emotions, and do not look for shiny objects as they are just distractions from the mundane. 

2. Boring essential tasks repeated for long periods of time is why companies succeed.

"A focused fool can accomplish more than a distracted genius." 

-THE Alex Hormozi

#NapkinNotes

I want to live a rare life and so I will have to be surrounded by rare people. And rare people, are by definition, rare. 

They are not common.

My hope is that the people I meet now are trying to go all the way with me.

Alex Hormozi Well said!
